casebody.data:
The State, ex rel. Wynn, Appellant, v. Baker, Supt., Appellee.

[Cite as State, ex rel. Wynn, v. Baker (1991), 61 Ohio St.3d 464.]

(No. 90-1725 Submitted April 16, 1991 Decided August 14, 1991.) *465 Turhan Wynn, pro se. Per Curiam.

We affirm the decision of the court of appeals. Habeas corpus relief is not available to appellant because the sentencing error, if there is one, is not jurisdictional. Blackburn, supra.

Judgment affirmed.

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Holmes, Douglas, Wright, H. Brown and Resnick, JJ., concur.
